0A. apt-get install etcnet
0B. apt-get install etcnet-full

1. vi /etc/sysconfig/network
Pay attention to NETWORKING and CONFMETHOD variables:
NETWORKING=yes
CONFMETHOD=etcnet

Note that FORWARD_IPV4, GATEWAY and GATEWAYDEV variables are
ignored by /etc/net.

2. Edit /etc/sysctl.conf and remove the lines that are present
in /etc/net/sysctl.conf.

3. chkconfig --list network
You may need to run 'chkconfig network reset' (known bug).

4. /etc/net is compatible with dhcpcd ONLY
